artifacts.summary: Modal saturation infrastructure implemented. Core theorem saturated_modal_backward proven without sorry. Single-family BMCS cannot be saturated so original sorry remains.

partial_progress.details: All 5 phases executed. Phases 1-4 fully completed. Phase 5 partially completed - infrastructure created but sorry not eliminated due to architectural limitation of single-family BMCS.

completion_data.completion_summary: Implemented modal saturation infrastructure for BMCS with sorry-free saturated_modal_backward theorem. Created ModalSaturation.lean (463 lines) with saturation predicate, witness family construction, and helper lemmas. The original sorry in Construction.lean remains because single-family BMCS cannot be modally saturated - this is a fundamental limitation requiring true multi-family construction.
